Senate Resolution 342
By: Senator Strickland of the 42nd
A RESOLUTION
1 Creating the Senate Study Committee on Certified Peer Specialists, Addiction Recovery
2 Programs, and Protocols; and for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, substance use disorders and mental illnesses affect millions of individuals of
4 all ages, races, and ethnic backgrounds as well as their families, friends, coworkers, and
5 communities; and
6 WHEREAS, an estimated 46 million Americans experienced a substance use disorder in
7 2022, and more than one million Georgians are in active addiction to alcohol and illegal and
8 prescription drugs; and
9 WHEREAS, on average, over 200 people die each day from overdose or fentanyl poisoning,
10 and over a quarter of a million Americans have died from a fentanyl overdose since 2018;
11 and
12 WHEREAS, substance use disorders impact not only the individual affected but also
13 marriages, families, the economy, and the healthcare system; and
